import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.boxplot(x='location', y='precipitation', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation across different locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Location')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_max', data=data, label='Max Temperature', color='red')
    sns.lineplot(x='date', y='temp_min', data=data, label='Min Temperature', color='blue')
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):

    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Wind')
    plt.ylabel('Max Temperature')
    plt.legend(title='Wind vs Temperature', loc='upper right')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    sns.barplot(x=weather_counts.index, y=weather_counts.values, palette='viridis')
    plt.xlabel('Weather Condition')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition across all locations?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
